# Personal Site – Architecture

## Goals
- Build by design (Figma/etc.): do not change colors, fonts, or spacing unless asked.
- Skeleton first; add functionality only when requested (forms, API, CMS, etc.).
- Next.js App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind. Deploy on Vercel.

## Structure
- **app/** – layout.tsx (minimal), page.tsx, (routes)/ for multi-page. No (store)/(dashboard)/api until requested.
- **components/ui/** – globals.css (design tokens: light/dark palette, spacing). No business logic in UI.
- **components/layout/** – Navbar, Footer, ThemeProvider. Keep layout minimal.
- **components/sections/** – section components; empty until design provided.
- **components/** – use arrow functions for components, export from index.ts. Do not use default exports for those components.
  const func : React.FC<funcProps>= ()=>{} - also do not forget type script for those funcProps defined as type funcProps = HtmlAttributes<HTMLDivElement>  the HTMLDivElement  define by the first container of the components if its div use diveElement
   if button so use buttonElement and so on. Also do not forget to add the props.children to the funcProps type if you want to use it in the component.
   and this is example of how to use it in the component:
    const func : React.FC<funcProps>= ({children,...props}) => {
     return (
          <div {...props}>
                {children}
          </div>
     )
    }
- **components/** – use React.FC type include imports if arrow functions is the main function or using React attributes (e.g. props.children). Otherwise, use regular function with explicit return type.
- **hooks/** – custom hooks when needed.
- **lib/** – utilities (e.g. cn). **constants/** – site config, routes. **types/** – shared types.


## SEO (every page)
- Each page exports `metadata`: title, description. Use template for title when needed.
- Use semantic HTML, one H1 per page, aria-labels where needed. Images: next/image; prefer WebP. Video: WebM when added.

## Styling
- Use design tokens from `components/ui/globals.css`. Do not introduce new colors/fonts without design.
- Dark mode: Tailwind class strategy (`.dark`). Theme toggle in Navbar. Refine when dark design is provided.

## i18n
- Hebrew only: `lang="he"`, `dir="rtl"` in root layout.

## Later (do not build until said)
- Admin dashboard, auth, blog logic, contact form backend, CRM, payments (Stripe), protected content.

## You dont create any SVG components until the design is provided. When you do, use next/image for optimization and accessibility.
- In case you dont have any SVg to use , create small div with the word (implement as css selector after and absolute) of the icon.

