# Design tokens (semantic Tailwind)

Tokens are defined in `src/lib/styles/globals.css` and exposed via `tailwind.config.js` and `@theme inline`.

## Groups

| Group        | Use |
|-------------|-----|
| **base**    | Page and content (main background, body text, default borders). |
| **baseInverse** | Inverted base (e.g. dark strip on light page). |
| **brand**   | Teal accent (CTAs, links, focus rings). |
| **info**    | Informational state (alerts, badges). |
| **negative** | Error/destructive state. |
| **positive** | Success state. |
| **warning** | Warning state. |
| **nav**     | Navbar only (bar bg, input, divider, link colors). |

## Slots

- **Background**: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary` (e.g. `bg-base-primary`, `bg-brand-primary`).
- **Border**: `default`, `subtle`, `accent` for base/baseInverse; `subtle`, `accent` for brand/info/negative/positive/warning (e.g. `border-base-default`, `border-brand-accent`).
- **Text**: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `onColor` (e.g. `text-base-primary`, `text-base-onColor`).
- **Nav**: `primary`, `input`, `divider` (bg/border); `link`, `link-hover`, `link-active` (text/border).

## Examples

- Page background: `bg-background` or `bg-base-primary`
- Body text: `text-foreground` or `text-base-primary`
- Muted text: `text-muted-foreground` or `text-base-secondary`
- Navbar: `bg-nav-primary`, `border-nav-primary`, `text-nav-link`, `ring-offset-nav-primary`
- CTA / brand: `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-brand-accent`, `ring-primary`

## Legacy aliases

These remain for existing components; prefer semantic classes when adding new UI:

- `background`, `foreground`, `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `muted-foreground`, `border`, `ring`